<br>
Your argument is flawed.<br>
<br>
Time factors in, obviously. Putting a &quot;bar of mana&quot; limitation leads to erroneous conclusions.<br>
<br>
Mathematically speaking, you cannot hold one factor constant (mana used) without influencing another factor (fight duration, for example).<br>
<br>
I don't know how to explain it more simply than that, except to say that if you only look at partial data, you cannot make proper conclusions. <br>
<br>
Even on the basis of the very LIMITED rules and contexts and assumptions some folks are using here to bolster a flawed argument, it has been shown that Mage &gt; Enchanter DPS for this case.  <br>
<br>
When given the FULL context of specialization, tools in the toolkit, alternative forms of damage, you can simply make no comparison, or statement of equivalence, at all.<br>
<br>
I should have kept my promise, I see, to bite my tongue on rebuttals, because this just becomes endless.<br>
<br>
I'll do so, now. =P<br>
<br>
If asked about this again, I'll just smile and say, &quot;You are absolutely right.&quot;<br>
<br>
Or, as mentioned before, maybe I'll just turn around, bend over, grab my butt cheeks and pretend to talk to you with my ass.<br>
<br>
I think a sense of humor about this absurdity is warranted, at this point.<br>
<br>
Bara<br>
